The paper deals with cyber security issues in networked control of a linear dynamical system, which suggests that it belongs to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses malicious attacks, which indicates that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The communication channel and packet losses suggest that it could also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of Lyapunov-like functions suggests that it could belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the exploration of attacks from the attacker's perspective suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
